headline: Expeditors posts upbeat results on higher freight volumes, customs fees
summary: Global freight forwarder Expeditors International of Washington reported second-quarter profit and revenue above Wall Street estimates on Tuesday, helped by higher airfreight and ocean container volumes and bigger custom fees. Airfreight tonnage and ocean container volume increased 7% each year-over-year for the quarter ended June 30, as companies rushed to import before new U.S. tariffs kick in. The company also benefited as increasingly complex trade policies allowed it to charge shippers higher processing fees.

headline: Expeditors (NYSE:EXPD) Delivers Strong Q2 Numbers
summary: Logistics and freight forwarding company Expeditors (NYSE:EXPD) reported Q2 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 8.7% year on year to $2.65 billion. Its GAAP profit of $1.34 per share was 7.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
